nd many of its reliant customers with energy derived from  renewable resources nrg energy completed its acquisition of genon energy in december  for  billion in stock and cash the genon name was retired in the merger but the combined company retained genons houston headquarters to coordinate operations in august  nrg acquired energy curtailment specialists a buffalo new york based demand response company the terms of the deal were not disclosed  a goal zero battery lamp and solar panel in september  nrg acquired goal zero a manufacturer of personal solar power products naming rightsedit nrg energy holds the naming rights to the nrg park campus in houston texas home to the nrg astrodome nrg stadium nrg arena and nrg center on march   nrg energy announced that they would be rebranding reliant park to replace reliant on all signages to nrg wholesale generationedit after the genon merger nrg has  mw of total generation capacity enough to power approximately  million homes its nearly  power plants are located in  states in the northeast chicago area gulf coast southwest nevada and california generation facilities include mostly fossil fuel power plants powered by natural gas oil and coal plus four wind farms in texas and six solar farms in california arizona and new mexico nrg also has a  ownership stake in the south texas nuclear generating station and a  stake in a coal power plant in gladstone queensland australia some facilities use cogeneration and the company also owns mw of solar distributed generation retail electricityedit nrgs retail power services provide electricity services to more than  million homes and businesses mostly in arizona and the northeastcitation needed green energy initiativesedit nissan leaf recharging from an evgo network charging station in houston texas beginning in  nrg began an initiative to become an green energy producer in the united states and started investing money in clean energy projects they include onshore and offshore wind power solar thermal energy photovoltaic and distributed solar power facilities and repowering of some of their traditional coal plants with biomass in late  nrg launched the evgo network the first completely private public car charging station network for electric power vehicles the company signed a twoyear agreement beginning in january  to provide  renewable energy for the empire state building assemblywoman aravella simotas has been chair of a coalition to support the utility in their plan to replace its decadesold dirty power plant in astoria with a newer generator the company stated its intention in  to replace  older oil generators with new gas generators that will increase the megawatts of power while reducing emissions see alsoedit new jersey portal new york portal houston portal energy portal renewable energy portal nuclear technology portal companies portal greenstreet nrg tower new york energy law referencesedit  a b c d nrg and genon complete merger creating nation’s largest competitive power generator business wire press release retrieved    a b nrg energy inc annual report form k united states securities and exchange commission february     a b c nrg energy inc annual report form k united states securities and exchange commission february     httpwwwnjcommercerindexssfwestwindsorofficialstoutsustainabilityelementsofnrgenergysnewmheadquartershtmlincartriver  httpwwwnjcommercerindexssfofficialsbreakgroundonnrgenergysnewheadquartersinwestwindsorhtmlincartriver  contact us nrg energy retrieved on july    carnegie center princeton nj   township of west windsor new jersey zoning map township of west windsor retrieved on july    exit revisited nrg energy inc  exelon bids for major texas power producer nrg houston chronicle october   retrieved on april   the plants were originally part of the former houston lighting  power the integrated utility that served the houston area until it was broken up into three separate companies as the state deregulated its power mar